main event: Two civilians reported observing a bright white object in the eastern sky over Duluth, Minnesota for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
interesting points: The object was stationary for most of the observation,The brightness of the object obscured the visibility of stars in the sky,The object disappeared when clouds moved in front of it,It was described as much brighter than a star and changing colors rapidly from orange to greenish blue,The witnesses included one individual and his wife who both observed the object.
sighted object: a bright white object changing colors in the sky
witness description: civilian, one of whom was an advertising business professional
